Ace Hardware Member Notice

I meant to reply earlier, but the afternoon got away from me and I just sat down again.
I did end up taking the longer path through the park, and it was absolutely the right decision because it cleared my head for the rest of the day.
The air felt cooler than I expected, and there were only a few people out, so everything seemed unusually calm.
I also listened to that playlist you sent, and I can see why you like it so much because it has a nice steady pace without being distracting.
After that I went home, tidied up the kitchen, watered the plants, and finally finished folding the laundry that had been waiting all week.
I am still thinking about your suggestion for the weekend, and I am leaning toward saying yes because it sounds easygoing and low pressure.
Let me know what time works best for you tomorrow since I should be around most of the morning.

Ace
Hardware

