Offer availability and eligibility are presented for review on the linked page. This email contains transaction-style account information for identification purposes only.

I was thinking about what you asked, and honestly I probably made it sound more complicated than it really is.
The main thing that helped was breaking everything into smaller tasks and doing one at a time instead of trying to finish all of it at once.
Once I stopped bouncing between different things, the whole day felt a lot more manageable and I was less distracted.
I also finally moved that chair near the window like you suggested, and now that corner actually feels usable instead of awkward.
It is funny how one small change can make a room seem calmer without needing to redo anything else around it.
I have not decided about Sunday yet, though I am tempted because being outside for a while sounds better than sitting around all afternoon.
If you are still up for it, send me the general plan when you have a minute and I will let you know as soon as I sort out the rest of my week.

